English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born in 1078, in Wales, United Kingdom. She had at least 3 sons with Llewelyn ap Gwrgan of Cydweli."},"et":{"1078?–":"1078–Surnud","1075–Male":"1075–Surnud","1104–Male":"1104–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1078–Female":"1078–Surnud","1104":"1104","1078?":"1078","1078":"1078","Abt 1104":"umbes 1104","1075":"1075","Wales":"Wales"},"fi":{"1078?–":"1078–Kuollut","1075–Male":"1075–Kuollut","1104–Male":"1104–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1078–Female":"1078–Kuollut","1104":"1104","1078?":"1078","1078":"1078","Abt 1104":"noin 1104","1075":"1075","Wales":"Wales"},"fr":{"1078?–":"1078–Décédée","1075–Male":"1075–Décédé","1104–Male":"1104–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1078–Female":"1078–Décédée","1104":"1104","1078?":"1078","1078":"1078","Abt 1104":"environ 1104","1075":"1075","Wales":"Galles","lifeSummary":"Joan est née en 1078, à Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 3 fils avec Llewelyn ap Gwrgan of Cydweli."},"de":{"1078?–":"1078–Verstorben","1075–Male":"1075–Verstorben","1104–Male":"1104–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1078–Female":"1078–Verstorben","1104":"1104","1078?":"1